H0.text: Take in light is what cells must do in order to grow at a normal rate.

H1.text: Be specialized is required for cells to grow at a normal rate.

H2.text: Taking in nutrients is necessary for cells to grow at a normal rate.

H3.text: Being of similar size is necessary for cells to grow at a normal rate.

A4.text: Cell proliferation typically involves balanced cell growth and cell division rates that maintain a roughly constant cell size in the exponentially proliferating population of cells.
